nts and customers who have the capital to pay for it. Cultivated through performances by security laborers, the sensation of security is a set of culturally shaped racialized and gendered impressions related to safety, order, well-being, and cleanliness. While the sensação de segurança indexes an outward-facing task of allaying fears of crime and maintaining order in elite spaces, it also refers to the emotional labor and embodied worlds that security workers navigate.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHuman securityzBrazil. 0aPrivate security serviceszBrazilxEmployees. 0aPrivate security serviceszBrazilxSociological aspects. 0aPublic safetyzBrazil. 0aRacism against Black peoplezBrazil. 0aUrban violencexSocial aspectszBrazil. 4aSOCIOLOGY & SOCIAL SCIENCE. 4aURBAN STUDIES. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Urban.2bisacsh  asecurity in Brazil, police violence in Brazil, racial capitalism in Brazil, private security in Rio de Janeiro, urban violence in Brazil, private security industry, racialized inequality in Brazil.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501769757?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501769757423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501769757/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b20